I have run across a number of greedy groups in my day.  One memorable time is in Highkeep, when the groups &quot;alpha&quot; loot just so happened to skip the letter &quot;K&quot; every round. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   That was also the MOST disorganized bunch of losers I have ever met, I really wish I could remember all your names. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway...That's why I typically don't get in pickup groups.  I usually group with a few friends, we loot whatever, and split it between us later.  Also, it's a trust thing as well, for the most part, I am very untrusting, and I don't want someone elses mistake messing me up.  Overall, NBG has worked for me though in groups, I'll just pipe up and say &quot;Hey, I am looking for item X&quot; and if it drops I will get it and be happy and keep killing stuff.  I do try to keep the number of items I ask for down though, and only participate in rolls if no one really wants the item. <p><center>Kundow Sylvanblaze, general destructive bastard, and best friend to bar owners all over Norrath</center>
